## Receipts

- `wzrrd templates list` reports `joel/tufte-mdsvx` as the user-default Tufte SvelteKit + MDSvX shell, backed by `system/tufte-mdsvx` and theme `tufte-notes`.
- `wzrrd init --template joel/tufte-mdsvx --slug summary-components-probe --title "Summary Components Probe" --emoji 🧠` generated a local probe site under `tmp/wzrrd-template-inspect/summary-components-probe`.
- The generated template includes `ReportLayout`, `MarginNote`, `PatternCards`, and `StatLine` components plus a document-first `src/routes/+page.svx`.
- Current bridge HUD rendering lives in `src/run-hud.ts`, `src/discord/progress-hud-machine.ts`, and `src/discord/payloads.ts`.

## Canonical home decision

Split the homes by responsibility:

- `joelhooks/pi-notes` should own the durable local Project Memory Portal layer: Document Host behavior, `.brain` discovery/rendering, session-history adapters, stable routes, and tailnet-safe URL reporting.
- `wzrrd` should own reusable visual recipes/components that need to be copied into static review/summary sites.
- `pi-discord-threads` should dogfood the first visible slice because its HUD/session-memory loop creates immediate product pressure and real receipts. It should emit/curate session memory data and consume verified portal URLs, not fork the whole portal stack.
